I think it's going to be
around for a very long time.

00:43:21.700 --> 00:43:22.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So you don't
see it collapsing?

00:43:22.830 --> 00:43:24.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: I don't.

00:43:24.010 --> 00:43:25.100 align:middle line:90%
I see it spreading.

00:43:25.100 --> 00:43:27.647 align:middle line:84%
Right now there are hundreds
of different coins being used--

00:43:27.647 --> 00:43:29.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's a
company, a brand-new one,

00:43:29.480 --> 00:43:32.090 align:middle line:84%
that deals with
selling coins to people

00:43:32.090 --> 00:43:34.100 align:middle line:90%
interested in the paranormal.

00:43:34.100 --> 00:43:35.535 align:middle line:90%
It's called Onstellar.

00:43:35.535 --> 00:43:36.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: That's great.

00:43:36.410 --> 00:43:38.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that's
what they're doing.

00:43:38.090 --> 00:43:40.670 align:middle line:84%
So they'll probably
be successful.

00:43:40.670 --> 00:43:42.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: I wouldn't bet on it.

00:43:42.680 --> 00:43:47.690 align:middle line:84%
So there's been such a success
with Bitcoin and Ethereum

00:43:47.690 --> 00:43:49.395 align:middle line:90%
and Litecoin, as we mentioned.

00:43:49.395 --> 00:43:51.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean, all these things
have been very successful.

00:43:51.520 --> 00:43:54.140 align:middle line:84%
They've gone up, so more and
more people are piling in.

00:43:54.140 --> 00:43:56.140 align:middle line:84%
It's a little bit
like a pyramid scheme.

00:43:56.140 --> 00:43:57.890 align:middle line:84%
Actually it's a lot
like a pyramid scheme.

00:43:57.890 --> 00:43:59.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Right,
it's a lot like it--

00:43:59.570 --> 00:44:00.810 align:middle line:90%
a lot like it.

00:44:00.810 --> 00:44:03.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: But it does have
the practicality behind it

00:44:03.320 --> 00:44:05.787 align:middle line:84%
of making for easy
digital transactions.

00:44:05.787 --> 00:44:07.370 align:middle line:84%
And these different
coins are designed

00:44:07.370 --> 00:44:10.110 align:middle line:84%
to be specialized for
different purposes.

00:44:10.110 --> 00:44:12.750 align:middle line:84%
And they can be very useful
for these different purposes.

00:44:12.750 --> 00:44:14.792 align:middle line:84%
You can keep track of
electrical power this way.

00:44:14.792 --> 00:44:16.250 align:middle line:84%
There's a coin
called Power Ledger.

00:44:16.250 --> 00:44:18.041 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, there are all
these different coins

00:44:18.041 --> 00:44:20.026 align:middle line:84%
that can be used for
different purposes.

00:44:20.026 --> 00:44:21.650 align:middle line:84%
The problem is there's
so many, there's

00:44:21.650 --> 00:44:23.892 align:middle line:90%
been such an explosion of coins.

00:44:23.892 --> 00:44:25.100 align:middle line:90%
They can't all be successful.

00:44:25.100 --> 00:44:29.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's a physicist
doing dabbling in this stuff?

00:44:29.120 --> 00:44:30.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: I gotta eat.

00:44:30.470 --> 00:44:33.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: All right, so you're
doing it as an investment?

00:44:33.000 --> 00:44:34.375 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: When I
see a wave coming,

00:44:34.375 --> 00:44:36.920 align:middle line:84%
you know, as an investment
wave, I try to get on it.

00:44:36.920 --> 00:44:43.040 align:middle line:84%
So whether that's in real
estate or cryptocurrency--

00:44:43.040 --> 00:44:45.520 align:middle line:84%
stocks is where I have
most of my experience--

00:44:45.520 --> 00:44:47.390 align:middle line:90%
I try to ride those waves.

00:44:47.390 --> 00:44:49.490 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I've been
financially successful

00:44:49.490 --> 00:44:50.630 align:middle line:90%
throughout my life.

00:44:50.630 --> 00:44:52.484 align:middle line:84%
I'm not wildly successful,
but I eat well.

00:44:52.484 --> 00:44:53.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So you're
doing all that.

00:44:53.900 --> 00:44:56.060 align:middle line:90%
You've moved to Maui.

00:44:56.060 --> 00:44:57.590 align:middle line:90%
Have you given up physics?

00:44:57.590 --> 00:44:59.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: Absolutely not.

00:44:59.040 --> 00:45:00.510 align:middle line:84%
This is just what
I do on the side

00:45:00.510 --> 00:45:01.400 align:middle line:90%
to fund the physics research.

00:45:01.400 --> 00:45:03.858 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: All right, so you're
still doing physics research.

00:45:03.858 --> 00:45:07.400 align:middle line:84%
So by moving to Maui you
didn't give up on life.

00:45:07.400 --> 00:45:10.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: No, I'm trying to
have as much life as I can.

00:45:10.340 --> 00:45:11.900 align:middle line:90%
Life in Maui is fantastic.

00:45:11.900 --> 00:45:14.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, let's take a
look at physics and surfing.

00:45:14.660 --> 00:45:16.616 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: Sure.

00:45:16.616 --> 00:45:20.102 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:45:20.102 --> 00:46:05.870 align:middle line:90%


00:46:05.870 --> 00:46:08.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So this is
a little push there

00:46:08.190 --> 00:46:09.680 align:middle line:90%
to tie that in the physics.

00:46:09.680 --> 00:46:13.360 align:middle line:84%
But where do you see,
Garrett, physics headed?

00:46:13.360 --> 00:46:16.500 align:middle line:84%
What's the next
evolution for us?

00:46:16.500 --> 00:46:19.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Well, ideally
what I'd like to do

00:46:19.170 --> 00:46:22.400 align:middle line:84%
is make more progress in
having a quantum description

00:46:22.400 --> 00:46:24.150 align:middle line:84%
of the geometry that
I've used to describe

00:46:24.150 --> 00:46:26.430 align:middle line:84%
elementary particles
and gravity and see

00:46:26.430 --> 00:46:29.225 align:middle line:84%
if I can get a quantized
description of the theory using

00:46:29.225 --> 00:46:30.850 align:middle line:84%
other advanced
mathematical structures.

00:46:30.850 --> 00:46:32.808 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are you going
to blow this planet wide

00:46:32.808 --> 00:46:35.335 align:middle line:90%
open with some new knowledge?

00:46:35.335 --> 00:46:37.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: I hope you're speaking
only in an abstract sense.

00:46:37.710 --> 00:46:38.940 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yes, of course.

00:46:38.940 --> 00:46:42.740 align:middle line:84%
We don't want you playing
around with protons and neutrons

00:46:42.740 --> 00:46:44.515 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:46:44.515 --> 00:46:46.026 align:middle line:90%
The atom, leave it alone.

00:46:46.026 --> 00:46:47.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Even though
I have a lair

00:46:47.400 --> 00:46:49.410 align:middle line:84%
on a volcano in the middle
of the Pacific Ocean,

00:46:49.410 --> 00:46:51.450 align:middle line:90%
I'm not actually a supervillain.

00:46:51.450 --> 00:46:54.550 align:middle line:84%
I'm really just trying to solve
the ultimate puzzles of nature

00:46:54.550 --> 00:46:55.350 align:middle line:90%
as best I can.

00:46:55.350 --> 00:46:57.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But what do
we need on this planet

00:46:57.210 --> 00:47:00.240 align:middle line:84%
to find out that we don't
really know right now?

00:47:00.240 --> 00:47:01.505 align:middle line:90%
What's the answer--

00:47:01.505 --> 00:47:03.005 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Well the
ultimate question--

00:47:03.005 --> 00:47:03.879 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --out there?

00:47:03.879 --> 00:47:05.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: The ultimate
question right now

00:47:05.730 --> 00:47:10.980 align:middle line:84%
is how to correctly
describe quantum gravity.

00:47:10.980 --> 00:47:12.210 align:middle line:90%
We don't currently have a--

00:47:12.210 --> 00:47:12.910 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What does that mean?

00:47:12.910 --> 00:47:13.826 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: --description.

00:47:13.826 --> 00:47:16.020 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: To a layman,
what's quantum gravity mean?

00:47:16.020 --> 00:47:18.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Well, currently we
have a good quantum description

00:47:18.990 --> 00:47:21.570 align:middle line:84%
of atoms and
elementary particles,

00:47:21.570 --> 00:47:26.430 align:middle line:84%
and we have a good description
of strong gravitational fields.

00:47:26.430 --> 00:47:32.490 align:middle line:84%
Like around stars, black
holes, our whole cosmos,

00:47:32.490 --> 00:47:34.040 align:middle line:84%
we have a good
description of that.

00:47:34.040 --> 00:47:38.280 align:middle line:84%
What we don't have is we don't
have a microscopic description

00:47:38.280 --> 00:47:39.630 align:middle line:90%
of gravity.

00:47:39.630 --> 00:47:42.270 align:middle line:84%
When we try to use quantum
mechanics to describe gravity,

00:47:42.270 --> 00:47:43.560 align:middle line:90%
we don't get good answers.

00:47:43.560 --> 00:47:46.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sir Isaac
Newton simply told us,

00:47:46.380 --> 00:47:48.780 align:middle line:84%
just drop two things,
that's gravity.

00:47:48.780 --> 00:47:50.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: People are trying that.

00:47:50.730 --> 00:47:55.260 align:middle line:84%
So they've done experiments
of microscopic objects dropped

00:47:55.260 --> 00:47:56.080 align:middle line:90%
in gravity.

00:47:56.080 --> 00:47:58.260 align:middle line:84%
And you can see how
quantum mechanics does

00:47:58.260 --> 00:48:00.750 align:middle line:84%
apply when things are in
a gravitational field,

00:48:00.750 --> 00:48:02.460 align:middle line:84%
but they can't have
a quantum description

00:48:02.460 --> 00:48:03.870 align:middle line:84%
of the gravitational
field itself.

00:48:03.870 --> 00:48:04.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Without gravity--

00:48:04.530 --> 00:48:06.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: There's no
such description.

00:48:06.030 --> 00:48:08.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Without
gravity could we exist?

00:48:08.320 --> 00:48:10.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Not in our
current form, no.

00:48:10.020 --> 00:48:11.357 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We'd be torn apart?

00:48:11.357 --> 00:48:13.440 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Well, you can think
of some organisms that

00:48:13.440 --> 00:48:16.470 align:middle line:84%
could exist in a
nongravitating cloud of matter.

00:48:16.470 --> 00:48:19.740 align:middle line:84%
But our entire
existence has evolved

00:48:19.740 --> 00:48:23.340 align:middle line:84%
on this planet where we have
a strong gravitational field

00:48:23.340 --> 00:48:25.590 align:middle line:84%
pulling us down towards
the center of the earth.

00:48:25.590 --> 00:48:29.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So if we get this
answer to that question,

00:48:29.380 --> 00:48:30.610 align:middle line:90%
what is the quantum gravity--

00:48:30.610 --> 00:48:32.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: How is
gravity quantized?

00:48:32.140 --> 00:48:34.310 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --what does
that mean to us?

00:48:34.310 --> 00:48:37.180 align:middle line:84%
How is that going to
change my day-to-day life?

00:48:37.180 --> 00:48:41.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Well, there will be some
beautiful bit of mathematics

00:48:41.260 --> 00:48:44.650 align:middle line:84%
underneath it that describes
how our universe functions

00:48:44.650 --> 00:48:45.850 align:middle line:90%
on a very fundamental level.

00:48:45.850 --> 00:48:48.550 align:middle line:84%
We'll have a unified theory
that describes both gravity

00:48:48.550 --> 00:48:49.967 align:middle line:90%
and particle physics.

00:48:49.967 --> 00:48:52.300 align:middle line:84%
And I would think you would
find it more philosophically

00:48:52.300 --> 00:48:54.820 align:middle line:84%
satisfying to know
that there is--

00:48:54.820 --> 00:48:56.530 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Does it put
food on my table?

00:48:56.530 --> 00:48:59.290 align:middle line:90%


00:48:59.290 --> 00:49:02.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: That's more about
permaculture farming

00:49:02.290 --> 00:49:05.050 align:middle line:84%
and other very high-quality
methods of living

00:49:05.050 --> 00:49:07.120 align:middle line:90%
than about fundamental physics.

00:49:07.120 --> 00:49:09.299 align:middle line:84%
But why do you want
the food on the table?

00:49:09.299 --> 00:49:11.590 align:middle line:84%
You have food on the table
so you can eat it, enjoy it,

00:49:11.590 --> 00:49:13.910 align:middle line:84%
and then spend your time
enjoying life and thinking

00:49:13.910 --> 00:49:14.710 align:middle line:90%
about stuff.

00:49:14.710 --> 00:49:16.251 align:middle line:84%
So what are you
going to think about?

00:49:16.251 --> 00:49:18.640 align:middle line:84%
What I choose to think
about is the deepest

00:49:18.640 --> 00:49:21.025 align:middle line:84%
puzzle I could find in the
universe, which is what is it?

00:49:21.025 --> 00:49:22.400 align:middle line:90%
What is the universe?

00:49:22.400 --> 00:49:23.200 align:middle line:90%
That's why I eat.

00:49:23.200 --> 00:49:25.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We may never
get that answer.

00:49:25.040 --> 00:49:26.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: We might
not live to see it.

00:49:26.540 --> 00:49:29.170 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to live longer if I
possibly can and get to see it.

00:49:29.170 --> 00:49:31.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you believe
in life after death?

00:49:31.420 --> 00:49:32.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: I barely believe in--

00:49:32.690 --> 00:49:33.940 align:middle line:90%
I believe in life during life.

00:49:33.940 --> 00:49:35.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You barely
believe in life, right?

00:49:35.750 --> 00:49:37.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: No, I don't believe
in life after death.

00:49:37.750 --> 00:49:39.875 align:middle line:84%
There's no evidence anything
like that would exist.

00:49:39.875 --> 00:49:42.100 align:middle line:84%
As far as we know,
our conscious minds

00:49:42.100 --> 00:49:44.410 align:middle line:84%
require a physical
substrate to exist.

00:49:44.410 --> 00:49:47.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you ever in your
life asked for something--

00:49:47.320 --> 00:49:49.630 align:middle line:84%
maybe there was someone in
your family that was sick

00:49:49.630 --> 00:49:50.800 align:middle line:90%
or whatever--

00:49:50.800 --> 00:49:54.840 align:middle line:90%
and said, God, please help me?

00:49:54.840 --> 00:49:55.640 align:middle line:90%
Ever?

00:49:55.640 --> 00:49:56.822 align:middle line:90%
Ever use that phrase?

00:49:56.822 --> 00:49:59.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Sure, when I was a
little kid inside my head.

00:49:59.030 --> 00:50:01.490 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Then why'd
you grow out of that?

00:50:01.490 --> 00:50:03.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: It never
got me anything.

00:50:03.430 --> 00:50:05.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yet.

00:50:05.130 --> 00:50:06.414 align:middle line:90%
Maybe it did.

00:50:06.414 --> 00:50:08.080 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it got you to
where you are today?

00:50:08.080 --> 00:50:10.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: If you keep talking
to yourself inside your head

00:50:10.100 --> 00:50:11.210 align:middle line:84%
and asking for
things, you're going

00:50:11.210 --> 00:50:12.590 align:middle line:84%
to get those things
some of the time.

00:50:12.590 --> 00:50:13.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:50:13.390 --> 00:50:16.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: But then
that doesn't mean

00:50:16.040 --> 00:50:18.320 align:middle line:84%
that some supernatural
power made it happen.

00:50:18.320 --> 00:50:19.650 align:middle line:90%
It just means that happened.

00:50:19.650 --> 00:50:23.104 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But could you accept
the fact that it's possible?

00:50:23.104 --> 00:50:24.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: If there was
any evidence for it

00:50:24.770 --> 00:50:28.070 align:middle line:84%
at all I'd have a higher
degree of belief in it.

00:50:28.070 --> 00:50:30.654 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you go to meetings
with your peers and colleagues?

00:50:30.654 --> 00:50:32.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Yeah, I
go to conferences.

00:50:32.070 --> 00:50:34.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And if so, what do they
think of the you, of your work?

00:50:34.820 --> 00:50:36.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: They think
I'm a little weird.

00:50:36.590 --> 00:50:37.390 align:middle line:90%
They also--

00:50:37.390 --> 00:50:38.900 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No!

00:50:38.900 --> 00:50:41.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: They also like
coming out to Maui to visit.

00:50:41.450 --> 00:50:44.260 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who wouldn't?

00:50:44.260 --> 00:50:47.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: Although I had an
unusual lifestyle hopping

00:50:47.100 --> 00:50:47.900 align:middle line:90%
around--

00:50:47.900 --> 00:50:52.230 align:middle line:84%
so after I got my PhD, I
didn't go to Maui immediately.

00:50:52.230 --> 00:50:55.961 align:middle line:84%
I spent time in
different friends' houses

00:50:55.961 --> 00:50:58.460 align:middle line:84%
where I spent time working on
physics while I took advantage

00:50:58.460 --> 00:51:00.150 align:middle line:90%
of their hospitality.

00:51:00.150 --> 00:51:02.600 align:middle line:10%
And I got a lot of good work
done while traveling around

00:51:02.600 --> 00:51:05.000 align:middle line:10%
to beautiful places
in the world working

00:51:05.000 --> 00:51:07.580 align:middle line:10%
on physics while staying
in friends' houses.

00:51:07.580 --> 00:51:10.390 align:middle line:84%
And I got the idea of
turning this into a thing.

00:51:10.390 --> 00:51:12.710 align:middle line:84%
We could have a network
of science hostels

00:51:12.710 --> 00:51:14.950 align:middle line:84%
where theoretical
researchers could go--

00:51:14.950 --> 00:51:15.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Not a bad idea.

00:51:15.950 --> 00:51:20.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISI: --and work on stuff in a
very low-stress, very enjoyable

00:51:20.300 --> 00:51:21.680 align:middle line:90%
environment.

00:51:21.680 --> 00:51:23.690 align:middle line:84%
So I had a hard time
persuading people

00:51:23.690 --> 00:51:25.940 align:middle line:84%
to give me their
houses for this,

00:51:25.940 --> 00:51:28.762 align:middle line:84%
but I had enough resources that
I bought my own house in Maui.

00:51:28.762 --> 00:51:30.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And now
you do your thing?

00:51:30.220 --> 00:51:32.200 align:middle line:10%
>>LISI: Now I run it as a
small science institute--

00:51:32.200 --> 00:51:32.540 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Good for you.

00:51:32.540 --> 00:51:33.830 align:middle line:10%
>>LISI: --called the
Pacific Science Institute.

00:51:33.830 --> 00:51:36.230 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Garrett, thanks for
being on "Beyond Belief".

00:51:36.230 --> 00:51:38.920 align:middle line:84%
You at least opened up our
minds to more possibilities--

00:51:38.920 --> 00:51:39.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISI: Good, I hope so.

00:51:39.920 --> 00:51:41.211 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --and I appreciate it.

00:51:41.211 --> 00:51:44.180 align:middle line:84%
We call him the
subversive physicist.

00:51:44.180 --> 00:51:46.020 align:middle line:10%
Now you know why.

00:51:46.020 --> 00:51:49.500 align:middle line:10%
I'm George Noory and thanks
for watching "Beyond Belief".

00:51:49.500 --> 00:51:55.392 align:middle line:90%